WEBVTT

00:01.377 --> 00:02.662
MOHINDER:
Previously on Heroes.

00:02.753 --> 00:05.085
And you see
what people want.

00:05.173 --> 00:06.379
Their desires,

00:06.465 --> 00:07.591
their hopes.

00:07.675 --> 00:08.710
I got your power.

00:08.801 --> 00:10.587
SAMUEL:
Isn't that
interesting?

00:10.678 --> 00:12.179
I know why
you can't kill.

00:12.263 --> 00:15.881
Hiro Nakamura said
you're going to die alone,
and it's haunting you.

00:16.517 --> 00:19.099
SAMUEL: We all need people
who understand us,
care for us.

00:19.187 --> 00:20.927
Who is she?
The love of my life.

00:21.022 --> 00:22.558
Just shows up.
He's stalking you?

00:22.648 --> 00:23.763
He does seem...

00:23.858 --> 00:25.143
Obsessed?

00:26.402 --> 00:28.814
I had to act to protect you,
to get you away from him.

00:28.905 --> 00:30.395
By kidnapping me?

00:31.365 --> 00:34.482
You can never
change the past.
It's bad. Always.

00:34.577 --> 00:35.783
Everything is connected!

00:35.870 --> 00:38.236
lfyou
wanna change one thing,
that's all you do.

00:38.331 --> 00:40.868
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:42.126 --> 00:44.082
I've come back
in time to save
Charlie.

00:44.170 --> 00:46.536
And this time,
lwi|| defeat
the Brain Man.

00:46.631 --> 00:47.620
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

00:51.135 --> 00:52.466
There's something
I want you to see.

00:52.595 --> 00:54.506
So magical,
so beautiful.

00:54.597 --> 00:56.087
Just let me show you,
that's all.

00:56.182 --> 00:58.343
If you're still unhappy,
I'll take you
right back to California.

00:58.601 --> 01:01.138
CLAIRE: Did they really
think that they were gonna
get away with it?

01:01.229 --> 01:02.935
Forever? That we would
just never find out?

01:03.022 --> 01:04.102
We shouldn't have
doneit

01:04.190 --> 01:07.353
I need time to grieve
without being reminded why.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.861
Do you want
to talk about it?

01:20.623 --> 01:21.783
About what?

01:21.874 --> 01:23.205
Life among the carnies?

01:23.292 --> 01:24.702
The death of your father?

01:24.794 --> 01:28.503
I mean, either one
of those would be enough
to mess me up.

01:28.589 --> 01:31.331
I don't think
I'd know where to start.

01:32.218 --> 01:36.632
I think it's one of those
things ljust have to
figure out by myself.

01:41.227 --> 01:45.766
Listen, I'm not gonna pretend
to know what you're going
through right now.

01:45.856 --> 01:49.519
But I want you to know
that I'm here for you,

01:49.610 --> 01:52.773
if you need anything,
anything at all.

01:57.994 --> 02:02.363
l have this
review-lesson thing.

02:03.374 --> 02:06.366
They moved it to Bapst Hall,
I have no idea where that is.

02:06.460 --> 02:09.122
East quad.
Clear across campus.

02:09.213 --> 02:12.046
(LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY)
Of course it is.

02:16.595 --> 02:18.256
(SIGHING)

02:18.347 --> 02:21.680
Excuse me,
is this seat taken?

02:46.083 --> 02:47.869
(AN DO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

02:49.337 --> 02:50.326
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

02:53.799 --> 02:55.175
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

03:00.848 --> 03:02.554
How's it coming?

03:04.018 --> 03:05.633
lt's ready.

03:05.728 --> 03:09.437
Now, remember,
it will only work in
the hands of one of us.

03:09.523 --> 03:12.185
LuckHy,
you have Hiro
and Ando now.

03:13.027 --> 03:15.018
You sure
I can't change
your mind?

03:15.112 --> 03:18.570
I broke a promise
to a girl. I need
to make amends.

03:19.283 --> 03:21.695
Well, then,
I guess this is it.

03:21.994 --> 03:24.155
(CHUCKLES)
In our lives,
when is it ever?

03:24.246 --> 03:25.986
Thanks, Mohinder.

03:26.916 --> 03:27.905
Good luck.

03:28.000 --> 03:29.080
You, too, Noah.

03:46.477 --> 03:49.264
Well, gentlemen,
I guess it's up to us.

03:50.064 --> 03:51.349
ANDO: Hiro?

04:03.994 --> 04:05.495
Hello, Carp.

04:05.704 --> 04:07.160
Adam Monroe?

04:08.833 --> 04:10.494
But you're dead.

04:11.794 --> 04:13.125
Am I dead?

04:13.212 --> 04:15.203
That's for the judge
to decide.

04:15.297 --> 04:16.286
Judge?

04:16.382 --> 04:17.713
WOMAN: AII rise.

04:17.800 --> 04:21.292
The honorable
Judge Kaito Nakamura
presiding.

04:22.430 --> 04:23.465
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

04:23.556 --> 04:24.591
WOMAN: Be seated.

04:25.057 --> 04:26.843
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

04:26.976 --> 04:30.434
The World v. Hiro Nakamura,
Your Honor.

04:30.729 --> 04:31.764
The what versus what?

04:31.856 --> 04:34.689
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

04:49.039 --> 04:50.199
(GROANING)

05:03.512 --> 05:06.549
Excuse me, is this
Professor Yanno's
review session?

05:06.640 --> 05:09.097
Nope. Study group.

05:12.897 --> 05:14.433
You ready
to brainstorm?

05:17.234 --> 05:19.520
What the hell
are you doing here?

05:20.279 --> 05:21.860
I came to learn.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.187
(DOOR OPENING)

06:03.781 --> 06:05.317
How'd you sleep?

06:06.242 --> 06:08.403
The dress is a gift.

06:08.494 --> 06:09.700
If you want to change
into something...

06:09.787 --> 06:13.780
A gift?
You kidnapped me.
Brought me to...

06:13.874 --> 06:15.034
(SIGHS)

06:15.125 --> 06:17.787
I don't even know
where we are because
you won't tell me.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.915
You're right. I'm sorry.
I never meant to upset you.

06:21.006 --> 06:23.497
I'll take you back
home straightaway.

06:26.262 --> 06:28.594
What? What are you
smiling about?

06:28.681 --> 06:30.797
Your face. Just now.

06:30.891 --> 06:34.475
It brought me back
to when I broke
your record player.

06:34.603 --> 06:36.139
(SIGHING) Samuel.

06:36.230 --> 06:40.143
You had this one song
you played over
and over and over.

06:40.234 --> 06:41.519
And I was just...

06:41.610 --> 06:44.147
l was just kidding around
but I broke the arm.

06:44.238 --> 06:45.478
(SIGHING)

06:45.573 --> 06:47.359
Remember?
Yes.

06:48.117 --> 06:49.152
I remember.

06:49.243 --> 06:50.323
Good.

06:50.828 --> 06:53.444
'Cause there's something
I still want you to see.

06:53.539 --> 06:56.155
The only thing
I'm interested
in seeing

06:56.250 --> 06:57.911
is my own front door.

06:58.002 --> 06:59.663
But first,
let me get you
something to eat.

06:59.753 --> 07:02.620
And then
you'll be rid of me
for good. I promise.

07:03.882 --> 07:05.622
This is how
it always starts.

07:05.718 --> 07:07.800
Breakfast becomes lunch.

07:07.886 --> 07:12.755
Lunch becomes dinner.
Dinner turns into drinks
and then...

07:13.350 --> 07:15.511
I fixed your record player.

07:17.855 --> 07:19.561
(SIGHING)

07:20.190 --> 07:22.567
I broke it
and then I fixed it.

07:22.776 --> 07:26.268
I know when I've done wrong.
And I know how
to make it good.

07:26.363 --> 07:31.903
Scotch tape and wire
hangers and loads
of good intentions.

07:40.628 --> 07:41.663
Fine.

07:42.546 --> 07:44.207
Something to eat.

07:44.715 --> 07:46.455
Then you take me home.

07:47.468 --> 07:48.799
Good. Great.

07:51.013 --> 07:53.800
He has a brain tumor,
in the parietal lobe.

07:53.891 --> 07:56.052
The doctors in Japan
said it's inoperable, but...

07:56.143 --> 07:57.724
We may not
have a choice.

07:57.811 --> 07:59.096
Please, Doctor,
he's my best friend.

07:59.188 --> 08:00.894
lcan'tjust...
Wait here.

08:00.981 --> 08:02.812
We'll find out
what's happening.

08:04.401 --> 08:07.313
KENSEI: It is our intent
to prove that the defendant
abused his power

08:07.404 --> 08:12.615
to bend space and time
selfishly and repeatedly
for his own personal gain,

08:12.701 --> 08:17.240
and with a blatant disregard
for the consequences
on the space-time continuum.

08:17.331 --> 08:20.823
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

08:27.883 --> 08:30.465
This is some bad dream
or tumor hallucination.

08:33.931 --> 08:35.637
This isn't a court.
It's a diner.

08:35.724 --> 08:39.467
Perhaps Your Honor could
enter a plea for the
defendant if he refuses.

08:39.603 --> 08:41.139
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

08:58.372 --> 09:01.864
KAITO: Mr. Monroe,
please call
your first witness.

09:01.959 --> 09:03.995
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:04.086 --> 09:06.793
The prosecution calls
Kimiko Nakamura...

09:06.880 --> 09:09.371
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:09.466 --> 09:11.673
...and Ando Masahashi.

09:21.478 --> 09:24.891
Do you know
how I would
love to kill you?

09:24.982 --> 09:26.142
Listen,

09:26.984 --> 09:28.349
I know you must hate me.

09:28.444 --> 09:30.605
You killed my father.

09:31.947 --> 09:33.187
Nathan.

09:34.616 --> 09:36.823
Seems like a lifetime ago.

09:37.369 --> 09:39.655
But I'm a little
off my game.

09:40.122 --> 09:41.987
And you're going
to help me get it back.

09:42.082 --> 09:43.367
Says who?

09:45.294 --> 09:46.750
Says this.

09:46.837 --> 09:50.421
Your face showing up
in ink wasn't my choice.

09:50.507 --> 09:54.125
lt's destiny
showing me my desire.

09:54.219 --> 09:55.959
And you actually
thought that I would...

09:56.054 --> 09:57.305
Relax.

09:59.057 --> 10:01.548
They told me
I need a connection.

10:02.895 --> 10:04.226
A friend.

10:05.898 --> 10:07.980
I don't want
to be alone,

10:09.401 --> 10:12.188
and somehow
you're supposed
to help me.

10:12.529 --> 10:15.191
I wouldn't help you
if my life depended on it.

10:15.282 --> 10:18.570
It's not your life
you should be
concerned about.

10:23.207 --> 10:24.663
Gretchen.

10:31.882 --> 10:33.793
Let's get this over with.

10:33.884 --> 10:35.795
You don't have
to hurt Gretchen.

10:35.886 --> 10:37.842
I promise that
you will see her again,

10:37.930 --> 10:41.593
just as soon as
you help me
answer my question.

10:41.683 --> 10:43.765
Here is what
I've been thinking.

10:43.852 --> 10:45.513
You and me.

10:46.730 --> 10:49.597
We got a lot in common.
We're both adopted.

10:51.235 --> 10:54.477
Abandoned by parents
who didn't want us

10:54.571 --> 10:58.905
and raised by parents
who didn't understand us.

10:58.992 --> 11:01.199
My parents
understand me just fine.

11:01.286 --> 11:02.822
Stop lying to yourself.

11:03.372 --> 11:05.988
Both of our dads
were cold-blooded killers,

11:06.083 --> 11:09.371
which is ironic,
because you and l

11:09.753 --> 11:14.918
cannot be killed.

11:15.509 --> 11:19.502
| get it, okay?
We have a few arbitrary
things in common.

11:19.596 --> 11:21.336
What is your point?

11:22.266 --> 11:24.882
My point is,
they're not arbitrary,

11:27.104 --> 11:28.514
they're formative.

11:29.022 --> 11:32.105
The basic
building blocks
of our lives.

11:32.526 --> 11:36.269
And we have
the same blocks,

11:36.363 --> 11:37.899
yet here we are,

11:38.907 --> 11:40.772
content college co-ed

11:41.785 --> 11:43.366
and me.

11:44.746 --> 11:47.078
How did we end up
so different?

11:50.544 --> 11:53.411
You want to know
what the difference is?

11:54.631 --> 11:57.122
You're a psychopath.

11:59.469 --> 12:01.050
Mystery solved.

12:03.223 --> 12:04.429
(GRUNTING)

12:06.310 --> 12:08.596
You think this is a game?

12:11.315 --> 12:16.230
This is my life.
You're supposed
to help me.

12:17.112 --> 12:23.824
Or don't you care how
many fillets l slice
your roommate into?

12:27.164 --> 12:29.746
If you're not going
to contribute,

12:29.833 --> 12:32.745
I'll just have
to take the answers
from your head.

12:32.836 --> 12:34.918
You're going to slice
my head open again?

12:35.005 --> 12:36.666
l've evolved
way beyond that.

12:36.798 --> 12:40.336
Our friend Lydia
gave me a much
more precise instrument.

12:40.427 --> 12:45.171
She could read someone
just by touching them.

12:45.807 --> 12:48.640
See into the very
depths of their soul.

12:49.311 --> 12:53.099
Of course her methods
were a little hyper-erotic,

12:54.358 --> 12:55.689
but what the hell.

12:58.028 --> 13:00.189
It is college,
isn't it?

13:10.332 --> 13:11.947
The dress suits you.

13:19.675 --> 13:21.131
What's that?

13:21.718 --> 13:23.549
Strawberry milkshake.

13:24.846 --> 13:26.382
Your favorite.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.226
That was a long time ago.

13:36.066 --> 13:37.476
(CLEARING THROAT)

13:37.567 --> 13:38.898
How about this one?

13:39.027 --> 13:41.814
The last time | crashed
in your dorm room,

13:41.905 --> 13:43.611
we talked all night.

13:43.740 --> 13:45.446
Among other things.

13:53.041 --> 13:54.656
You talked about
your dream home.

13:54.751 --> 13:57.037
That was
the tequila talking.

13:57.963 --> 14:02.297
"A peaceful cottage
surrounded by nature
and happiness."

14:04.761 --> 14:06.752
You're such a romantic.

14:08.390 --> 14:11.723
Actually, that's something
I've admired about you.

14:13.228 --> 14:16.391
But there comes a time
when you have to realize

14:17.232 --> 14:20.190
that you're never
going to have that cottage.

14:20.277 --> 14:21.642
Says who?

14:27.242 --> 14:28.357
Can you honestly tell me

14:28.452 --> 14:31.660
you don't look back
at our time together
with a hint of fondness?

15:08.867 --> 15:10.653
NURSE: What's your prognosis?
DOCTOR: Not good.

15:10.744 --> 15:12.700
I wouldn't normally
do this procedure...

15:16.208 --> 15:19.871
(KENSEI SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:25.634 --> 15:29.593
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:31.598 --> 15:33.338
(KENSEI SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:36.478 --> 15:38.764
KENSEI: The witness
hasidenﬂﬁed
Hiro Nakamura,

15:38.855 --> 15:41.517
who's clearly and selfishly
interfered with the timeline.

15:41.650 --> 15:42.981
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:43.068 --> 15:45.059
(KAITO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:55.831 --> 15:57.446
(HIRO REPLYING IN JAPANESE)

16:03.421 --> 16:07.164
Just so I'm clear,
on your personal scale
of temporal justice,

16:07.259 --> 16:10.717
it's okay so long
as no one gets hurt?

16:13.223 --> 16:15.885
Yes. That is my definition.

16:16.726 --> 16:18.512
That's good to know

16:18.603 --> 16:21.561
because I believe
my next witness is here.

16:26.945 --> 16:28.481
CLAIRE:
Just tell me where she is.

16:29.239 --> 16:33.107
Claire Bennet,
you've been holding
out on me.

16:33.243 --> 16:35.108
What are you talking about?

16:36.246 --> 16:38.658
Why I was supposed
to find you.
You and l are the same.

16:38.748 --> 16:40.739
lam nothing like you.

16:40.834 --> 16:42.950
You do exactly what I do.

16:43.920 --> 16:49.916
You use this gift,
this curse, whatever it is,
to build walls,

16:50.635 --> 16:54.469
make it impossible
to actually connect
with another person.

16:55.849 --> 16:57.430
Like Gretchen.

16:58.018 --> 16:59.007
(EXCLAlMlNG)

16:59.102 --> 17:02.060
All those memory hits
I got from your stuff
while I was tying her up

17:02.147 --> 17:03.387
have such
a different context now.

17:03.481 --> 17:06.769
Everything in that room
is so full of

17:08.111 --> 17:09.521
pauses.

17:09.654 --> 17:11.360
What did you say?

17:11.990 --> 17:17.451
Pauses.
All these moments
so ripe with subtext.

17:19.289 --> 17:21.371
"Can I borrow your book?"

17:23.001 --> 17:25.538
"Cut my hand
with these scissors."

17:27.130 --> 17:29.166
All these interactions,

17:29.299 --> 17:34.009
and you still can't say
the one thing you really
want to say to this girl.

17:34.804 --> 17:35.964
Heck,

17:36.681 --> 17:39.593
you keep this up,
you might end up
alone forever, too.

17:39.684 --> 17:42.221
You don't know
what you're talking about.

17:42.479 --> 17:43.969
I think I do.

17:45.023 --> 17:46.809
The indestructible girl

17:50.237 --> 17:51.647
(CHUCKLES)

17:53.031 --> 17:55.864
What? No angry retort?

17:57.410 --> 17:59.321
(SCREAMING)

18:00.080 --> 18:02.321
You're right.
You are off your game.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.827
You just told me
exactly where she is.

18:11.424 --> 18:14.211
How many people
have I killed?

18:15.262 --> 18:16.968
Hundreds, I suppose.

18:17.097 --> 18:20.555
And all of this because
of an agreement you made
with the defendant?

18:20.642 --> 18:23.304
Yep. He told me
if I saved the waitress,

18:23.395 --> 18:26.307
I could have the cheerleader
and anybody else
I wanted to kill.

18:26.398 --> 18:28.764
KENSEI: And as long as
you saved his girlfriend,

18:28.858 --> 18:31.270
you could kill
some more.
Willy-nilly.

18:31.361 --> 18:32.441
Willy-nilly.

18:32.529 --> 18:35.441
Seems to me that
a lot of people were hurt

18:35.532 --> 18:38.023
as a result of
Mr. Nakamura's
time-tampering.

18:38.201 --> 18:39.190
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

18:50.463 --> 18:53.250
Really? Does this
look right to you?

18:54.551 --> 18:57.543
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

19:01.016 --> 19:06.181
Tell me again, who else met
their death by your hand
after Hiro made this deal?

19:06.271 --> 19:09.479
Well, there was her.
And Eden-ish.

19:09.566 --> 19:13.900
Two Primatech guards.
The melty guy.
The mechanic.

19:13.987 --> 19:18.526
lsaac Mendez. My mother.
Some guy named Ted something.

19:18.616 --> 19:23.906
And so on, and so on.
If Hiro was acting
out of nobility,

19:23.997 --> 19:26.613
perhaps he should
have stopped
this vicious killer

19:26.708 --> 19:28.198
before these
countless murders...

19:28.293 --> 19:30.830
Sprague. Ted Sprague.

19:30.920 --> 19:34.287
See, saving Charlie wasn't
for the heroic good,

19:35.050 --> 19:37.132
it was for
the good of Hiro.

19:37.218 --> 19:40.631
No. Romantic or not,
Charlie was a good person.

19:40.930 --> 19:43.922
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

19:53.401 --> 19:54.390
KENSEI: Fair enough.

19:54.486 --> 19:57.944
Then the prosecution
would like to call
its final witness.

19:58.323 --> 19:59.938
Charlie Andrews.

20:04.996 --> 20:08.033
That's right.
I forgot. We can't
bring Charlie in

20:08.124 --> 20:12.083
because this
world-improving person
is lost in time.

20:12.170 --> 20:14.331
Now tell me,
how did that happen,
again?

20:14.839 --> 20:16.454
I made a deal with the...

20:16.549 --> 20:18.881
I'm sorry,
you have to speak up.

20:19.803 --> 20:23.341
I made a deal with
a villain, and he
double-crossed me.

20:25.016 --> 20:26.256
Right.

20:28.770 --> 20:31.352
The prosecution rests,
Your Honor.

20:36.986 --> 20:40.319
SAMUEL: A shake roof,
wrap-around porch

20:40.407 --> 20:46.118
and a stone path leading
to a lake where the sun
glistens over the water.

20:46.204 --> 20:47.410
How'd you remember
all of that?

20:47.497 --> 20:48.782
l have my ways.

20:50.083 --> 20:51.619
I know all the details.

20:51.709 --> 20:53.745
By heart, it would seem.

20:53.837 --> 20:55.452
Hard to forget.

20:58.007 --> 21:00.043
l was holding
you close to me.

21:00.135 --> 21:01.875
And the way
you painted it

21:02.804 --> 21:04.010
(SIGHING)

21:04.097 --> 21:07.635
made it so real,
like it came
from your soul.

21:07.934 --> 21:09.595
Like it was you.

21:09.727 --> 21:12.594
You always know
the right thing to say.

21:13.565 --> 21:16.523
You have the perfect
scrap of poetry
in your pocket to...

21:16.609 --> 21:17.894
To what?

21:18.903 --> 21:20.939
(SIGHING)

21:25.910 --> 21:29.744
The big oak tree
in the yard surrounded
by wildflowers.

21:29.831 --> 21:33.915
And a couple of
rocking chairs on the deck
to watch the sunset.

21:37.422 --> 21:39.083
You do remember.

21:46.055 --> 21:47.966
(SIGHING)

21:57.859 --> 22:00.566
With a fireplace
to keep us warm.

22:01.029 --> 22:03.941
And a summer breeze
to keep us cool.

22:07.619 --> 22:09.280
How do you do it?

22:11.039 --> 22:15.874
Every single time.

22:31.768 --> 22:34.931
This is so beautiful.
How did you do this?

22:35.021 --> 22:37.763
My friends and I can do
the most amazing things.

22:37.857 --> 22:39.768
Look.
There's your dream cottage.

22:39.859 --> 22:41.850
No more traveling now.
We're making a home,
a real home.

22:41.945 --> 22:44.357
For me, for you.
If you'll have me.

22:44.447 --> 22:45.857
(SIGHS)

22:46.199 --> 22:47.359
Sam.

22:48.201 --> 22:51.989
You said you couldn't
join a carnival.
But now you don't have to.

22:52.080 --> 22:55.993
There's no more
carriage homes,
no more main homes. Just...

22:56.584 --> 22:57.994
Just that.

22:58.419 --> 23:01.081
Away from everything.
It's what you talked about.

23:01.172 --> 23:03.037
It could be our life.

23:09.013 --> 23:11.220
I can't live here.

23:12.058 --> 23:13.047
But you said...

23:13.142 --> 23:15.599
I know, I know,
I know what I said.

23:15.937 --> 23:17.347
It's just that
I didn't think
you'd actually...

23:17.438 --> 23:18.427
Actually do it?

23:18.523 --> 23:19.603
Yeah.

23:19.691 --> 23:22.649
But... I mean...

23:23.570 --> 23:27.279
This dress and
the milkshake and...

23:28.449 --> 23:31.361
All of this.
This is a fantasy.

23:31.452 --> 23:34.580
And I made it come true.
For you.

23:34.664 --> 23:37.497
No, Sam. For you.

23:38.418 --> 23:40.249
This is your fantasy.

23:41.588 --> 23:46.002
And it's beautiful.
And I'm happy for you.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.636
But it isn't me.

23:53.516 --> 23:55.757
My life isn't here.

23:55.893 --> 23:57.508
Butlchanged
everything for...

23:57.604 --> 23:59.811
Don't tell me
you did all
of this for me.

23:59.897 --> 24:04.732
Please, don't...
Don't tell me
this was all for me.

24:11.659 --> 24:13.445
No, of course not.

24:14.621 --> 24:18.113
Listen, I should
get you back home.

24:19.208 --> 24:20.618
Thank you
for indulging me.

24:20.710 --> 24:21.699
Sam.

24:21.794 --> 24:23.204
No, it was really...

24:29.510 --> 24:32.092
It was really nice
to see you again.

24:48.988 --> 24:51.900
Gretchen. Gretchen.

24:52.742 --> 24:54.027
Are you okay?

24:54.118 --> 24:56.530
I'm fine.
All things considered.

24:56.621 --> 24:59.078
I'm so sorry.
This is all my fault.

24:59.165 --> 25:02.202
You never
should have gotten
caught up in it.

25:02.293 --> 25:06.536
I'm just...
I'm happy you're here.
And that it's over.

25:08.966 --> 25:11.582
It is over, isn't it?

25:12.887 --> 25:15.299
No. He's not done...

25:22.105 --> 25:23.060
Somewhere out in the open?

25:23.147 --> 25:24.307
No. He'll be
expecting that.

25:24.440 --> 25:25.816
He's trying
to flush us out.

25:25.942 --> 25:27.603
How do you know?

25:27.694 --> 25:30.561
'Cause apparently,
I get the way he thinks.

25:31.280 --> 25:32.816
Someone's coming.

25:32.907 --> 25:33.942
ln here.

25:39.664 --> 25:43.452
So, Sylar, huh?
The Sylar?

25:44.168 --> 25:48.787
Yes. Well, no. Kind of
the emo-apologist version.

25:48.965 --> 25:52.173
He's had me
trying to figure out
what his issues are.

25:52.301 --> 25:54.337
Seriously?
How'd that go?

25:55.513 --> 25:57.299
Pencil in the eye.

26:01.561 --> 26:03.301
Listen, I'm sorry.

26:04.230 --> 26:07.688
It's okay.
Getting used to being
all Perils of Pauline.

26:07.817 --> 26:11.309
No, not about that.
Well, yes,
about that, but...

26:14.407 --> 26:16.068
...about breakfast.

26:17.577 --> 26:21.490
About sometimes
keeping you
at arm's length.

26:21.914 --> 26:23.779
It's cool.
Are you kidding?

26:23.875 --> 26:24.910
If you don't want to...

26:25.001 --> 26:26.616
I do want to.

26:26.711 --> 26:31.922
ljust... I'm scared.
And I get afraid that
I'm gonna get hurt.

26:32.008 --> 26:37.002
And so I use
my "specialness"
to build these walls

26:37.096 --> 26:39.963
instead ofjumping
off bridges.

26:41.517 --> 26:45.476
I suck at metaphors,
but what I'm trying
to say is that...

26:46.189 --> 26:47.929
It's okay, really.

26:48.024 --> 26:50.390
No. No, it's not.

26:52.862 --> 26:54.693
This guy, Sylar,

26:56.157 --> 27:00.150
he sat there and told me
that we're very much alike.

27:00.244 --> 27:02.030
And he's not wrong.

27:02.413 --> 27:04.449
And I'm afraid
that I'm going
to end up alone

27:04.540 --> 27:07.407
for the rest
of my life,
like him.

27:07.502 --> 27:09.993
And I don't know
how to fix it.

27:12.215 --> 27:14.501
Do you want
to talk about it?

27:16.093 --> 27:21.258
I like to think of myself
as just a girl who happens
to have powers,

27:21.390 --> 27:24.678
and it's just one thing
in a list of attributes.

27:25.019 --> 27:29.888
Loyal, friendly,
regenerative, good skin.
You know?

27:29.982 --> 27:31.563
You do have good skin.

27:31.651 --> 27:33.312
(LAUGHS)

27:33.402 --> 27:37.361
But when you put
the chips down
and life gets tough,

27:39.242 --> 27:44.532
I hide behind
that one label,
that one attribute.

27:45.414 --> 27:47.700
And | close myself off.

27:51.712 --> 27:54.840
No wonder
Sylar is so messed up.

27:54.924 --> 27:58.883
I can only imagine
what having
a bunch of excuses

27:58.970 --> 28:01.382
could do to
someone's humanity.

28:02.098 --> 28:04.089
Maybe that's his answer.

28:04.642 --> 28:06.007
In order to become
human again,

28:06.102 --> 28:09.139
he has to get rid
of all of his powers.

28:10.147 --> 28:11.762
Yeah, maybe.

28:17.738 --> 28:19.444
Now was that so hard?

28:19.574 --> 28:21.280
You son of a bitch.

28:21.993 --> 28:23.449
Where is she?

