28:34.547 --> 28:35.957
Like I said,

28:37.592 --> 28:40.800
I've been having
a little trouble
being myself.

28:59.488 --> 29:00.773
Gretchen?

29:02.992 --> 29:04.698
(SIGHS)

29:04.785 --> 29:05.911
You're okay.

29:05.995 --> 29:07.280
Yeah.

29:07.622 --> 29:09.158
Of course I'm okay.

29:09.248 --> 29:12.615
Well, some guy
stole my backpack, but...
What's with you?

29:12.710 --> 29:16.077
Nothing. I'm fine,
and you're here,
and you're all right.

29:16.172 --> 29:18.458
Claire, you're
acting really weird.

29:18.549 --> 29:21.336
I'm sorry. I'm really
lucky to have you.

29:21.427 --> 29:24.009
And I'm sorry
about this morning.

29:25.181 --> 29:26.921
Forget it.
You know me.

29:27.016 --> 29:29.928
Impulsive Gretchen
wants to hold hands,
so she does it.

29:30.019 --> 29:33.261
I know, and I love that
about you. And I want
to be more like that.

29:33.356 --> 29:38.316
Not be beholden
to any label or definition

29:38.402 --> 29:41.018
or who I'm supposed
to be. ljust...

29:43.699 --> 29:45.815
I want to hold your hand.

29:52.083 --> 29:54.119
People are gonna
start to talk.

29:54.210 --> 29:55.700
Let 'em talk.

29:56.087 --> 29:59.329
Talking's good.
In fact, I could
use some talking

29:59.423 --> 30:02.085
if you still have
a sympathetic ear.

30:04.470 --> 30:07.883
l, in fact,
have two ears.

30:10.226 --> 30:11.511
